

Following are some of the major international news stories scheduled to be covered or pursued by Xinhua on Monday.

-- Exit polls show that opposition candidate Manuel Zelaya leads Sunday's presidential election in Honduras, winning more than 50 percent of the vote.

-- Ice on the wings of the West Caribbean Airways (WCA) airplane had caused the Colombian company's plane to crash in Venezuela, killing the 160 people on board on Aug. 16 this year, Colombian media said on Sunday.

-- Jordan has a new cabinet on Sunday, which faces the tasks of fighting against terrorism and improving the country's economy.

